The article is a transcript of President Joe Biden's speech at a Women's History Month celebration at the White House. He starts by joking about being Jill Biden's husband and introduces the diverse members of Congress and Cabinet present. He mentions Kamala Harris not being able to attend due to her husband's COVID-19 diagnosis. Biden highlights the achievements of women in his administration and the importance of gender equality. He signs an executive order promoting pay equality and equity for federal contractors. Biden mentions the U.S. Women's National Soccer Team and their fight for equal pay. He emphasizes the importance of gender equality for society, the economy, and the country as a whole. Biden concludes by introducing Jill Biden and expressing his love for her.